SIMPLE: flocculent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flocculent
<hw>Floc"cu*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Flock</er> of wool.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Clothed with small
flocks or flakes; woolly.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Applied to the down of newly
hatched or unfledged birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having a structure like shredded
wool, as some precipitates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flocculus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
